item.title: [634]Semi-Rewritten Runetekk Client
item.dc:creator: @sinisoul sini
item.description:
@sinisoul wrote:

perryman:

Bro, i code better than him…

[quote=“Davidi2, post:20, topic:433684”][quote author=sinisoul link=topic=536402.msg3922071#msg3922071 date=1329807241]

interesting stuff, still looks like the same old client if you can sift through the bullshit

exactly. its more abstraction and some new goodies but that’s about it. the skeleton is the same.
[/quote]Well yea, that sort of thing happens when you update the same game…

But I’d also attribute the fact you’re familiar with the 317 client, so when you rename things you’re going to be looking for the similarities, which is a big fac tor towards the overall ‘look’. The ones you don’t refactor are most likely the ones that are less familiar – thus the lack of discernible differences when only looking at the renamed parts.[/quote]

I’m assuming that you are talking to me since you quoted me. Yes, I am very familiar with the 317 but most of my naming in this release comes from my 414 client refactor and my 602 client refactor. I’m always going to look for similarities because jagex is a large company and making large random differences in the way they compile their game clients is going to cost time. Time costs money. Money costs profit. So in my client I could show you the origin of all the names and when exactly those started to appear. Because in all likelyhood if it’s a large system, such as the toolkits or on demand piece, it’s not going to change. Which is great because I can quickly sort out what is new and what isn’t. I focus on discovering pieces of the client that directly relate to what I’m currently emulating. (ondemand is completely rewritten because I’m working on that, lobby is semi rewritten because I was finding the packets I needed to start working on that)

Edit:

Well, for example, even though they don’t name file index 29 ‘varbit’ in the client, it’s still there. Same with floors and landscape archives etc. Anyway,

If any of you didn’t notice there is a ton of hints on how jagexs server is structured. Seeing that there are two different classes between game/lobby server packets and those used to initially connect.
